      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Installation Supervision and Commissioning</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Service engineer(s) supervise the installation process
and performs the commissioning of the systems on site.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">The supervision
includes the follow inspections:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Location and environment for the system and battery</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">System and battery wiring connections</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Internal power and communication components</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">The commissioning process also
includes:<ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Check and record measurements for the system input, system
output and voltage for each individual cell</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">A battery bank discharge test</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">If necessary, additional calibrations and adjustments</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Preventive Maintenance</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Yearly preventive maintenance</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">4-6 years preventive maintenance, minor material replacement</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">8-10 years preventive maintenance, major material replacement</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Corrective Maintenance</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Our service
engineers are available to assist on-site in the event that technical
repairs or part replacement services are needed.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Spare Parts</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <ul class="- topic/ul ">
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Spare parts used during commissioning </p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Spare parts used during preventive maintenance</p>
               </li>
               <li class="- topic/li ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">Strategical and critical spare parts to have on stock, with
a spare parts and interchangeability record (SPIR)</p>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Updates, Upgrades and Modifications</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Software and firmware updates to the latest revision with the
latest functions.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">During a system’s lifespan customer
needs might change and modifications might be necessary. Optional
features may be added to existing systems for example a network management
card (NMC) or a battery management system (BMS).</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Digital Services</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Monitor and
manage critical assets on site or remotely with high cyber security
can increase efficiency. It can help to efficiently operate selected
systems and reduce operation costs with flexible service plans.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Retrofit or Replace</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Retrofit: </b> Replace an existing system with the same design and dimensions as
the existing system.</p>
            <p class="- topic/p ">
               <b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Replace: </b> Replace an existing system
with a new design meeting the latest industry requirement.</p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
      <section class="- topic/section ">
         <title class="- topic/title ">Site Audit</title>
         <sectiondiv class="- topic/sectiondiv ">
            <p class="- topic/p ">Reality system have
a designed lifetime of 20 years, during this time your site might
grow or change. Reality can assist with a detailed on-site check to: <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Prepare for future service recommendations</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Discuss retrofit or replacement for systems nearing expected
end of life</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Organize installed base</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p class="- topic/p ">Review of the site environment for external factors that can
affect the system</p>
                  </li>
               </ul>
            </p>
         </sectiondiv>
      </section>
